The paper presents an approach to adaptively utilize deep neural networks for efficient inference, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on reducing the evaluation time of deep neural networks for image recognition tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
